<h2>5. How Contests Work</h2>
<h3>5.1 Contest Format</h3>
<p>BattlePicks offers peer-to-peer DFS pick'em Contests ("Props Battle"). Each Contest requires you to select a minimum of three (3) Picks on individual player statistical performances (e.g., points, rebounds, assists). Picks must satisfy the following structural requirements:</p>
<p>(a) A minimum of three (3) Picks per Contest entry;
(b) Each Pick must be on a different player (one Pick per player);
(c) Picks must span at least two (2) different teams;
(d) No more than one (1) overlapping player between matched Users.</p>
<h3>5.2 Matching</h3>
<p>Contest entries are matched automatically by the platform based on format, currency, and entry amount. You cannot choose, challenge, or request a specific opponent. Matching is designed to ensure fairness and prevent collusion.</p>
<p>If no opponent is found before the first game in your entry begins, your entry will be automatically canceled and your entry fee refunded.</p>
<h3>5.3 Scoring</h3>
<p>Each Pick is scored using a points system based on the payout multiplier (decimal odds) of the selected line at the time the entry was locked. Riskier predictions earn more points if correct. The User with the higher total points across all Picks wins the Contest.</p>
<h3>5.4 Settlement</h3>
<p>Contests are settled automatically after all games included in the Contest have been completed and final player statistics are available.</p>
<p>Settlement edge cases:
- <strong>Did Not Play (DNP):</strong> If a player does not participate in the game, that Pick is scored as a Push (1.0 points).
- <strong>Injury During Game:</strong> If a player is injured during a game, the Pick is graded based on the player's final statistical line.
- <strong>Postponed or Canceled Games:</strong> If a game is postponed or canceled and no final statistics are available within 24 hours of the originally scheduled start time, the affected Pick is voided (scored as Push, 1.0 points).
- <strong>Missing Statistical Data:</strong> If statistical data is unavailable within 24 hours after game completion, the affected Pick may be placed under manual review. BattlePicks will make reasonable efforts to obtain the data and grade the Pick accurately.
- <strong>Ties:</strong> If both Users score the same total points, the Contest is declared a tie and both Users receive a full refund of their entry fee.
- <strong>All Picks Voided:</strong> If all Picks in a Contest are voided, both Users receive a full refund of their entry fee and no Rake is charged.</p>
<h3>5.5 Rake</h3>
<p>BattlePicks charges a Rake of 5% on each completed Contest. The Rake is deducted from the total prize pool before the winner is paid. For example, if two Users each enter $10, the total pool is $20, the Rake is $1.00, and the winner receives $19.00.</p>
